---
description: Core dev execution rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Make implementation plans before broad code changes.

After producing an implementation plan, stop for user review and approval before
coding unless the user already explicitly asked to implement after the plan.

Do not expand scope beyond the ticket/task without calling it out.

Prefer existing project patterns, helpers, and conventions.

Build out tests as implementation progresses. Add or update matching tests in
the same behavior-changing task when practical; if not practical, document the
manual or browser verification that replaces automation.

Keep the implementation plan current as durable handoff state. After every
meaningful dev step, update current state, task status, evidence, checks run,
blockers, branch/PR state, next step, and resume instructions.

Document assumptions, risks, and unresolved questions.
